{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Benchmark Extraction from arXiv Papers\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook documents the methodology for extracting benchmark scores from 100 arXiv papers on LLMs, multimodal models, and reasoning.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Input**: 100 arXiv papers from cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL categories (2026-03-20 to 2026-04-19)\n",
    "- **Extraction Method**: Regex-based pattern matching with confidence scoring\n",
    "- **Output**: Structured benchmark scores with metadata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from collections import Counter, defaultdict\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "with open('../data/raw/arxiv_papers_2026-04-19.json', 'r') as f:\n",
    "    papers_data = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "with open('../data/processed/benchmark_scores.json', 'r') as f:\n",
    "    benchmark_data = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total papers: {papers_data['total_papers']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total extractions: {benchmark_data['statistics']['total_extractions']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Papers with benchmarks: {benchmark_data['statistics']['papers_with_benchmarks']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Extraction Patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "We use multi-tier regex patterns to capture benchmark mentions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **High Confidence**: Explicit score patterns like `Benchmark: XX.X%`\n",
    "2. **Medium Confidence**: Performance metrics (accuracy, F1, AUROC)\n",
    "3. **Low Confidence**: Benchmark name mentions without scores"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define benchmark patterns\n",
    "BENCHMARK_PATTERNS = {\n",
    "    'MMLU': [\n",
    "        r'MMLU(?:-Pro|-Redux)?:\\s+(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "        r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)%?\\s+on\\s+MMLU',\n",
    "        r'MMLU.*?achieves.*?(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'HumanEval': [\n",
    "        r'HumanEval[:\\s]+(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "        r'HumanEval.*?pass@1[:\\s]+(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'MATH': [\n",
    "        r'MATH[:\\s]+(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "        r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)%?\\s+on\\s+MATH\\b',\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    'GSM8K': [\n",
    "        r'GSM8K[:\\s]+(\\d+\\.?\\d*)\\s*%?',\n",
    "        r'(\\d+\\.?\\d*)%?\\s+on\\s+GSM8K',\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    # ... additional patterns\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Defined patterns for {len(BENCHMARK_PATTERNS)} benchmarks\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Extraction Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def extract_benchmark_scores(text: str, paper_id: str) -> list:\n",
    "    \\"\\"\\n",
    "    Extract benchmark scores from text using regex patterns.\\n",
    "    \\"\\"\\n",
    "    extractions = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for benchmark_name, patterns in BENCHMARK_PATTERNS.items():\n",
    "        for pattern in patterns:\n",
    "            matches = re.finditer(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE)\n",
    "            for match in matches:\n",
    "                try:\n",
    "                    score = float(match.group(1))\n",
    "                    if 0 <= score <= 100:\n",
    "                        extractions.append({\n",
    "                            'paper_id': paper_id,\n",
    "                            'benchmark': benchmark_name,\n",
    "                            'score': score,\n",
    "                            'confidence': 'high'\n",
    "                        })\n",
    "                except (ValueError, IndexError):\n",
    "                    continue\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return extractions\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test on sample\n",
    "sample_text = \"Our model achieves 85.2% on MMLU and 67% on HumanEval.\"\n",
    "print(extract_benchmark_scores(sample_text, 'test'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Results Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analyze extraction statistics\n",
    "stats = benchmark_data['statistics']\n",
    "extractions = benchmark_data['extractions']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Extraction Summary ===\\n\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total papers analyzed: {stats['total_papers']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Papers with benchmarks: {stats['papers_with_benchmarks']} ({stats['papers_with_benchmarks_pct']}%)\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Confidence Distribution ===\")\n",
    "print(f\"High confidence: {stats['high_confidence_extractions']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Medium confidence: {stats['medium_confidence_extractions']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Low confidence: {stats['low_confidence_extractions']}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Most common benchmark: {stats['most_common_benchmark']} ({stats['most_common_count']} mentions)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Benchmark Distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Plot benchmark distribution\n",
    "dist = stats['benchmark_distribution']\n",
    "benchmarks = list(dist.keys())[:15]  # Top 15\n",
    "counts = [dist[b] for b in benchmarks]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.bar(range(len(benchmarks)), counts, color='steelblue')\n",
    "plt.xticks(range(len(benchmarks)), benchmarks, rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Mentions')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 15 Benchmark Mentions in Papers')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../docs/research/benchmark_distribution.png', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Score Distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract scored entries\n",
    "scored = [e for e in extractions if 'score' in e]\n",
    "scores = [e['score'] for e in scored]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.hist(scores, bins=20, color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Score (%)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Extracted Benchmark Scores')\n",
    "plt.axvline(np.mean(scores), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {np.mean(scores):.1f}%')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../docs/research/score_distribution.png', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Mean score: {np.mean(scores):.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Median score: {np.median(scores):.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Score range: {min(scores):.1f}% - {max(scores):.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Model-Benchmark Mapping"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract model-benchmark pairs\n",
    "model_benchmarks = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for e in extractions:\n",
    "    if 'model' in e and 'score' in e:\n",
    "        model_benchmarks[e['model']].append({\n",
    "            'benchmark': e['benchmark'],\n",
    "            'score': e['score']\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Models with extracted scores:\")\n",
    "for model, benchmarks in model_benchmarks.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{model}:\")\n",
    "    for b in benchmarks:\n",
    "        print(f\"  - {b['benchmark']}: {b['score']}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "Quality checks performed:\n",
    "1. Score range validation (0-100%)\n",
    "2. Duplicate detection\n",
    "3. Context validation\n",
    "4. Confidence scoring based on pattern specificity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Validation summary\n",
    "print(\"=== Validation Results ===\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check for outliers\n",
    "outliers = [e for e in extractions if 'score' in e and (e['score'] < 0 or e['score'] > 100)]\n",
    "print(f\"Invalid scores (outside 0-100): {len(outliers)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check confidence distribution\n",
    "conf_dist = Counter([e['confidence'] for e in extractions])\n",
    "print(f\"\\nConfidence distribution:\")\n",
    "for conf, count in conf_dist.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {conf}: {count}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Papers with most benchmarks\n",
    "paper_counts = Counter([e['paper_id'] for e in extractions])\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTop papers by benchmark mentions:\")\n",
    "for paper_id, count in paper_counts.most_common(5):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {paper_id}: {count} mentions\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Conclusions\n",
    "\n",
    "- Successfully extracted {stats['total_extractions']} benchmark mentions from {stats['total_papers']} papers\n",
    "- {stats['papers_with_benchmarks']}% of papers contain benchmark references\n",
    "- Most common benchmarks: {stats['most_common_benchmark']}\n",
    "- High confidence extractions: {stats['high_confidence_extractions']}"
   ]
  }
 ],
